 fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: The provider''s physical security controls at their data centers. → This approach either ignores the issue, escalates prematurely without documentation, or follows an unstructured process that creates audit gaps. Auditors must always follow structured procedures.  Option B: The frequency of data backup and restoration testing performed by the provider. → This option misses the audit objective or applies the wrong standard. Audit procedures must be aligned with scope and audit standards (ISACA, COBIT).  Option D: The complexity of the encryption algorithms used to protect customer data at rest and in transit. → This might be a procedural step but not the complete or correct response. Context matters in audit decisions.'),
  ('CISA-00907', 4, 'Medium', 'Backup and Recovery Strategies', 'What should the auditor FIRST recommend to mitigate the risk of continued revenue loss during future peak seasons?', 'Performing a full penetration test of the payment processing system to identify vulnerabilities.', 'Updating the disaster recovery plan to include cloud-specific recovery procedures and testing the updated plan with simulated peak loads.', 'Implementing a robust intrusion detection system (IDS) to prevent future website outages.', 'Increasing server capacity to handle anticipated peak traffic volume.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Updating the disaster recovery plan to include cloud-specific recovery procedures and testing the updated plan with simulated peak loads.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Performing a full pen