  ('CISA-00910', 4, 'Medium', 'Backup and Recovery Strategies', 'What should the auditor FIRST recommend to improve the backup and recovery process for virtual machines?', 'Implementing a more frequent backup schedule for critical virtual machines.', 'Developing and implementing a formal process for periodically testing the recovery of individual virtual machines from backups.', 'Migrating all virtual machines to a geographically diverse secondary data center for redundancy.', 'Enforcing multi-factor authentication for all administrators accessing the virtualization platform.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Developing and implementing a formal process for periodically testing the recovery of individual virtual machines from backups.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Implementing a more frequent backup