nd allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Implementing a more frequent backup schedule for critical virtual machines. → This approach either ignores the issue, escalates prematurely without documentation, or follows an unstructured process that creates audit gaps. Auditors must always follow structured procedures.  Option C: Migrating all virtual machines to a geographically diverse secondary data center for redundancy. → This option misses the audit objective or applies the wrong standard. Audit procedures must be aligned with scope and audit standards (ISACA, COBIT).  Option D: Enforcing multi-factor authentication for all administrators accessing the virtualization platform. → This might be a procedural step but not the complete or correct response. Context matters in audit decisions.'),
