mmitments  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: The cost-effectiveness of the cloud backup storage. → Reactive recovery takes too long and increases business impact. Proactive monitoring and redundancy are essential.  Option C: The physical security controls at the cloud provider''s data centers. → Relying solely on backup restoration without redundancy causes unacceptable downtime. Modern resilience requires both prevention and rapid recovery.  Option D: The compatibility of the cloud backup solution with the on-premises backup tools. → Plans are useless if not tested. Untested disaster recovery plans typically fail when actually needed.'),
