  ('CISA-00925', 4, 'Medium', 'Backup and Recovery Strategies', 'What is the MOST important action for the auditor to take?', 'Review the service level agreement (SLA) with the cloud provider to ensure adequate backup and recovery provisions are in place.', 'Recommend that the business continuity plan be updated to include the new cloud-based system and its specific recovery requirements.', 'Verify that the cloud provider is SOC 2 compliant to ensure security and availability controls are adequate.', 'Test the cloud provider''s recovery procedures to ensure they meet the company''s recovery time objective (RTO) and recovery point objective (RPO).', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Recommend that the business continuity plan be updated to include the new cloud-based system and its specific recovery requirements.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT