res: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Ensuring that the tape drives are compatible with the encryption algorithms used. → This approach either ignores the issue, escalates prematurely without documentation, or follows an unstructured process that creates audit gaps. Auditors must always follow structured procedures.  Option C: Confirming that the backup schedule aligns with the company''s recovery point objective (RPO). → This option misses the audit objective or applies the wrong standard. Audit procedures must be aligned with scope and audit standards (ISACA, COBIT).  Option D: Assessing the speed and efficiency of the tape backup process. → This might be a procedural step but not the complete or correct response. Context matters in audit decisions.'),
