  ('CISA-00939', 4, 'Medium', 'Business Continuity and Disaster Recovery', 'What should the auditor FIRST recommend to management?', 'Negotiate a higher uptime guarantee with the primary payment gateway provider.', 'Develop and document a detailed procedure for switching to the fallback payment processing system and conduct regular testing.', 'Implement a real-time data replication solution for the payment gateway to minimize data loss.', 'Procure a second, independent payment gateway from a different vendor as a backup.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Develop and document a detailed procedure for switching to the fallback payment processing system and conduct regular testing.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Negotiate a higher uptime guarantee with the primary payment gateway provider. → This approa