  ('CISA-00946', 4, 'Hard', 'Business Continuity and Disaster Recovery', 'What is the auditor''s MOST important recommendation to address this contractual gap?', 'Negotiate a service level agreement (SLA) with the cloud provider that includes clearly defined RTO and RPO targets and associated penalties for non-compliance.', 'Implement local data caching mechanisms to minimize the impact of potential service disruptions on transaction monitoring capabilities.', 'Develop a manual workaround to enable transaction monitoring using alternative data sources in case of a cloud service outage.', 'Increase the frequency of BCP testing to identify and address potential weaknesses in the cloud-based failover process.', 'A', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (A): Negotiate a service level agreement (SLA) with the cloud provider that includes clearly defined RTO and RPO targets and associated penalties for non-compliance.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediati