omated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: The lack of separation of duties between application administrators and security personnel. → This approach either ignores the issue, escalates prematurely without documentation, or follows an unstructured process that creates audit gaps. Auditors must always follow structured procedures.  Option C: The inability to perform forensic analysis of the inventory management system in case of a security incident. → This option misses the audit objective or applies the wrong standard. Audit procedures must be aligned with scope and audit standards (ISACA, COBIT).  Option D: The risk of performance degradation on the inventory management system due to log storage. → This might be a procedural step but not the complete or correct response. Context matters in audit decisions.'),
  ('CISA-00985', 4, 'Hard', 'Monitoring and Logging', 'What is the MOST important recommendation the auditor should make regarding the cloud logging configuration?', 'Immediately enable all available logging options offered by the cloud provider to ensure comprehensive monitoring.', 'Conduct a risk assessment to identify critical events and prioritize the collection of specific log types relevant to those risks.', 'Negotiate a discounted rate with the cloud provider to enable all available logging options without increasing costs.', 'Implement a third-party security information and event management (SIEM) solution to collect and analyze logs from the cloud platform.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Conduct a risk assessment to identify critical events and prioritize the collection of specific log types relevant to those risks.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up a