  ('CISA-00990', 4, 'Hard', 'Monitoring and Logging', 'What is the MOST important concern for the auditor regarding the logging of the urgent system patch?', 'The absence of logging prevents the university from demonstrating compliance with regulatory requirements for patch management.', 'The lack of logging hinders the ability to verify the successful implementation of the patch and assess potential system instability.', 'The missing log data may indicate a wider problem with the organization''s overall logging policies and procedures.', 'The inability to identify the user who initiated the patch creates a security risk of potential unauthorized modifications.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): The lack of logging hinders the ability to verify the successful implementation of the patch and assess potential system instability.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up aud