  ('CISA-00992', 4, 'Hard', 'Monitoring and Logging', 'What is the MOST important control an auditor should recommend to improve monitoring and logging capabilities in this supply chain context?', 'Implement network intrusion detection systems (IDS) at the perimeter of the company''s network to detect unauthorized access.', 'Develop and implement standardized data exchange protocols and logging across all supply chain partner systems, with centralized monitoring and alerting within the company''s security information and event management (SIEM) system.', 'Require all suppliers to undergo annual security audits and penetration testing to ensure their systems meet minimum security standards.', 'Establish a dedicated incident response team to handle supply chain disruptions and data breaches.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Develop and implement standardized data exchange protocols and logging across all supply chain partner systems, with centralized monitoring and alerting within the company''s security information and event management (SIEM) system.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you commun