  ('CISA-00994', 4, 'Hard', 'Monitoring and Logging', 'What should the auditor FIRST advise to ensure effective and cost-efficient log management in this cloud environment?', 'Implement data compression techniques to reduce the storage footprint of the logs.', 'Establish a clear retention policy for logs based on regulatory requirements and business needs, and implement automated log archiving and deletion processes.', 'Integrate the centralized logging solution with a security information and event management (SIEM) system for real-time threat detection.', 'Enforce strict access controls for the centralized logging solution to prevent unauthorized access to sensitive data.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Establish a clear retention policy for logs based on regulatory requirements and business needs, and implement automated log archiving and deletion processes.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance pur