  ('CISA-00997', 4, 'Hard', 'Monitoring and Logging', 'What is the MOST important control deficiency for the auditor to highlight?', 'Lack of encryption for sensitive log data on the shared network drive.', 'Insufficient storage capacity allocated to the shared network drive.', 'Absence of a formal data retention policy for the transaction monitoring logs.', 'Inadequate network bandwidth affecting the speed of log data transfer.', 'A', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (A): Lack of encryption for sensitive log data on the shared network drive.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option B: Insufficient storage capacity allocated to the shared network drive. → This approach either ignores the issue, escalates prematurely without documentation, or follows an unstructured process that creates audit gaps. Auditors must always follo