  ('CISA-01003', 4, 'Medium', 'Monitoring and Logging', 'What should the auditor FIRST recommend to improve the integrity and usability of the audit logs?', 'Implement a centralized log management system with built-in time synchronization capabilities.', 'Enforce the use of a Network Time Protocol (NTP) server across all systems generating audit logs.', 'Deploy a Security Information and Event Management (SIEM) system to analyze the unsynchronized logs.', 'Increase the retention period of the audit logs to compensate for the lack of time synchronization.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Enforce the use of a Network Time Protocol (NTP) server across all systems generating audit logs.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Implement a centralized log management system with built-in time synchronization capabi