  ('CISA-01041', 4, 'Hard', 'System Maintenance and Patching', 'What is the MOST effective control the auditor should recommend to mitigate the risk associated with delayed patch deployment in this environment?', 'Implement a formal exception handling process for critical patch deployments, requiring management approval and justification for any delays.', 'Establish a dedicated test environment that mirrors the production environment to thoroughly evaluate the impact of patches on the supply chain systems.', 'Negotiate service level agreements (SLAs) with system vendors that guarantee minimal disruption during patch deployments.', 'Implement a rollback plan for each patch deployment to quickly revert to the previous system state if issues arise.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Establish a dedicated test environment that mirrors the production environment to thoroughly evaluate the impact of patches on the supply chain systems.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Cl