  ('CISA-01042', 4, 'Hard', 'System Maintenance and Patching', 'What should be the auditor''s FIRST recommendation regarding this finding?', 'Immediately revoke unrestricted privileges for the database team and implement a least-privilege access model.', 'Implement multi-factor authentication (MFA) for all database team members to mitigate the risk of privilege misuse.', 'Implement detailed audit logging for all database activities to monitor the database team''s actions.', 'Conduct a thorough risk assessment to identify potential vulnerabilities introduced by the unrestricted privileges.', 'D', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (D): Conduct a thorough risk assessment to identify potential vulnerabilities introduced by the unrestricted privileges.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Immediately revoke unrestricted pr