  ('CISA-01045', 4, 'Hard', 'System Maintenance and Patching', 'What is the auditor''s PRIMARY concern regarding this practice?', 'The lack of formal documentation for these changes may hinder future troubleshooting efforts.', 'The absence of CAB review increases the risk of introducing instability or unintended consequences to the production environment.', 'The bypassing of standard change management procedures may violate internal policies and regulatory compliance requirements.', 'The system administrators lack adequate technical expertise to properly assess the impact of these ''urgent system patches''.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): The absence of CAB review increases the risk of introducing instability or unintended consequences to the production environment.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: T