  ('CISA-01046', 4, 'Hard', 'System Maintenance and Patching', 'What should the auditor recommend as the MOST critical control to address this situation?', 'Implement a formal change management process for all operating system patches, including impact assessment and CAB approval.', 'Increase the frequency of penetration testing on the database servers to identify any vulnerabilities introduced by the patches.', 'Automate application-level regression testing after each patch deployment, even if it requires additional resources.', 'Develop a comprehensive rollback plan for operating system patches in case they cause application instability or data corruption.', 'C', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (C): Automate application-level regression testing after each patch deployment, even if it requires additional resources.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPT