ciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Accept the cloud provider''s attestation based on their reputation and industry certifications. → This approach either ignores the issue, escalates prematurely without documentation, or follows an unstructured process that creates audit gaps. Auditors must always follow structured procedures.  Option B: Conduct penetration testing on the cloud-based file-sharing service to verify the effectiveness of the encryption mechanisms. → This option misses the audit objective or applies the wrong standard. Audit procedures must be aligned with scope and audit standards (ISACA, COBIT).  Option D: Implement data loss prevention (DLP) controls to mitigate the risk of data exposure, regardless of the encryption status. → This might be a procedural step but not the complete or correct response. Context matters in audit decisions.'),
  ('CISA-01069', 4, 'Hard', 'Operations Security Controls', 'What should the auditor FIRST recommend?', 'Immediately disable the VPN connection and alert the vendor to reconfigure their access using multi-factor authentication.', 'Initiate a detailed review of all VPN configurations, focusing on access control lists (ACLs), intrusion detection system (IDS) alerts and logging for anomalous traffic.', 'Implement network segmentation to isolate the SCADA network from the corporate network, limiting the impact of potential breaches.', 'Conduct a vulnerability scan of the SCADA system and apply all available security patches to address known weaknesses.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Initiate a detailed review of all VPN configurations, focusing on access control lists (ACLs), intrusion detection system (IDS) alerts and logging for anomalous traffic.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis f