  ('CISA-01070', 4, 'Hard', 'Operations Security Controls', 'What is the auditor''s PRIMARY concern regarding this incident response plan?', 'The plan''s effectiveness in meeting regulatory compliance requirements related to environmental protection and worker safety.', 'The plan''s ability to quickly restore IT systems to normal operation following a disruptive cyberattack.', 'The plan''s integration with the refinery''s overall business continuity plan and disaster recovery plan.', 'The plan''s coverage of post-incident activities, such as root cause analysis and lessons learned.', 'A', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (A): The plan''s effectiveness in meeting regulatory compliance requirements related to environmental protection and worker safety.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option B: The plan''s ability to quickly