ng, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option B: The plan''s ability to quickly restore IT systems to normal operation following a disruptive cyberattack. → This approach either ignores the issue, escalates prematurely without documentation, or follows an unstructured process that creates audit gaps. Auditors must always follow structured procedures.  Option C: The plan''s integration with the refinery''s overall business continuity plan and disaster recovery plan. → This option misses the audit objective or applies the wrong standard. Audit procedures must be aligned with scope and audit standards (ISACA, COBIT).  Option D: The plan''s coverage of post-incident activities, such as root cause analysis and lessons learned. → This might be a procedural step but not the complete or correct response. Context matters in audit decisions.'),
  ('CISA-01071', 4, 'Hard', 'Operations Security Controls', 'What action should the auditor FIRST recommend regarding the third-party service provider relationship?', 'Immediately terminate the contract with the service provider and migrate the monitoring functions to an alternative vendor.', 'Conduct an urgent, independent security audit of the service provider''s environment, focusing on the scope of the breach and affected data.', 'Implement enhanced data encryption and access controls on the data shared with the service provider.', 'Review the service level agreement (SLA) with the service provider to determine the liabilities and compensation for the data breach.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Conduct an urgent, independent security audit of the service provider''s environment, focusing on the scope of the breach and affected data.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future