mplementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Implement a data loss prevention (DLP) solution to prevent future breaches of classified information. → This approach either ignores the issue, escalates prematurely without documentation, or follows an unstructured process that creates audit gaps. Auditors must always follow structured procedures.  Option C: Conduct a penetration test to identify vulnerabilities in the systems storing classified information. → This option misses the audit objective or applies the wrong standard. Audit procedures must be aligned with scope and audit standards (ISACA, COBIT).  Option D: Increase the frequency of security awareness training for employees handling classified information. → This might be a procedural step but not the complete or correct response. Context matters in audit decisions.'),
  ('CISA-01120', 5, 'Medium', 'Data Classification and Handling', 'What is the auditor''s PRIMARY concern regarding data handling during the migration process?', 'Ensuring the data migration tool is compatible with the existing SCADA system to prevent data corruption.', 'Verifying that the data is encrypted during transit and at rest in the cloud environment, according to the company''s data classification policy.', 'Confirming that all data migration activities are completed within the specified timeframe to minimize disruption to operations.', 'Validating that the cloud provider has implemented robust physical security controls to protect the data center housing the data.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Verifying that the data is encrypted during transit and at rest in the cloud environment, according to the company''s data classification policy.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Ensuring the data migration tool is compatible with the existing SCADA system to prevent data corruption. → This approach either ignores the issue, escalates prematurely without documentation, or follows an unstructured process that creates audit gaps. Auditors must always follow structured procedures.  Option C: Confirming that all data migration activities are completed within the specified timeframe to minimize disruption to operations. → This option misses the audit objective or applies the wrong standard. Audit procedures must be aligned with scope and audit standards (ISACA, COBIT).  Option D: Validating that the cloud provider has implemented robust physical security controls to protect the data center housing the data. → This might be a procedural step but not the complete or correct response. Context matters in audit decisions.', 'The auditor''s PRIMARY concern should be verifying that sensitive data is protected during transit and at rest in the cloud. This ensures confidentiality and integrity, aligning with the company''s data classification policy and protecting against unauthorized access or data breaches during and after the migration.', 'See reasoning above for explanation of correct vs incorrect choices', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Verifying that the data is encrypted during transit and at rest in the cloud environment, according to the company''s data classification policy.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation