  ('CISA-01138', 5, 'Medium', 'Encryption and Key Management', 'What should the auditor FIRST recommend to address this gap in control?', 'Implementing a data retention policy to reduce the volume of archived data.', 'Establishing a documented procedure for verifying the backup and secure storage of encryption keys.', 'Migrating the archived data to a cloud-based storage solution with built-in encryption and key management.', 'Performing regular data restoration tests from the tape backups to ensure data integrity.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Establishing a documented procedure for verifying the backup and secure storage of encryption keys.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Implementing a data retention policy to reduce the volume of archived data. → This approach either ignores the issue, escalat