  ('CISA-01143', 5, 'Hard', 'Encryption and Key Management', 'What should the auditor FIRST recommend to mitigate the risks associated with the abandoned temporary keys?', 'Implement a comprehensive vulnerability scanning program to identify other weaknesses in the database server configuration.', 'Develop and implement a formal key destruction policy and procedure, including secure deletion methods and chain of custody documentation.', 'Rotate the current production encryption keys to invalidate any data potentially accessed using the compromised temporary keys.', 'Implement a data masking solution to protect sensitive data in the ERP system in case of a breach.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Develop and implement a formal key destruction policy and procedure, including secure deletion methods and chain of custody documentation.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow