ols are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Implement multi-factor authentication (MFA) for all user accounts to enhance overall security posture. → This approach either ignores the issue, escalates prematurely without documentation, or follows an unstructured process that creates audit gaps. Auditors must always follow structured procedures.  Option C: Implement role-based access control (RBAC) based on job functions to streamline access provisioning. → This option misses the audit objective or applies the wrong standard. Audit procedures must be aligned with scope and audit standards (ISACA, COBIT).  Option D: Deploy a centralized logging and monitoring system to detect and respond to unauthorized access attempts. → This might be a procedural step but not the complete or correct response. Context matters in audit decisions.'),
  ('CISA-01159', 5, 'Hard', 'Access Control and Identity Management', 'What is the MOST important control the auditor should recommend to mitigate the risk of unauthorized access from partner organizations?', 'Implement periodic penetration testing of the federation service to identify vulnerabilities.', 'Establish a robust Service Level Agreement (SLA) with the partner organization outlining their responsibilities for timely user deprovisioning.', 'Implement automated account synchronization and deprovisioning between the telecom company''s IAM system and the partner organizations'' IAM systems.', 'Require all partner employees to undergo mandatory security awareness training.', 'C', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (C): Implement automated account synchronization and deprovisioning between the telecom company''s IAM system and the partner organizations'' IAM systems.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes