d with maintaining two separate patching systems. → This approach has a critical flaw: [specific reason why wrong answer is problematic relative to context]  Option C: Potential for conflicts between patches applied to IT and OT/ICS environments. → This is incomplete or applies the wrong standard. It might address part of the issue but misses the full picture.  Option D: Reduced efficiency in the IT environment due to the complexity of the automated patching system. → While seemingly reasonable, this approach deviates from best practice and creates unnecessary risk or inefficiency.'),
