  ('CISA-01193', 5, 'Hard', 'Data Loss Prevention', 'What is the auditor''s PRIMARY concern regarding data loss prevention in this scenario?', 'The potential financial impact of supply chain disruptions and production delays.', 'The effectiveness of the company''s third-party risk management program and its ability to detect and respond to security incidents affecting suppliers.', 'The technical security controls implemented by the supplier to protect the company''s sensitive data.', 'Ensuring compliance with industry-specific regulations related to data privacy and protection.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): The effectiveness of the company''s third-party risk management program and its ability to detect and respond to security incidents affecting suppliers.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: The pote