  ('CISA-01195', 5, 'Hard', 'Data Loss Prevention', 'What is the MOST important data loss prevention control the auditor should recommend implementing for contract engineers'' BYOD devices?', 'Mandatory installation of a corporate-approved antivirus solution on all BYOD devices.', 'Implementation of containerization or mobile device management (MDM) solutions to isolate corporate data and applications from personal data on the BYOD devices.', 'Mandatory security awareness training for all contract engineers regarding data protection and BYOD policies.', 'Regular security audits of the contract engineers'' BYOD devices to ensure compliance with company security policies.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Implementation of containerization or mobile device management (MDM) solutions to isolate corporate data and applications from personal data on the BYOD devices.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purp